(589, 2, 'Sarah Gayle Carter', '/images/temp_storage/2011_07_18_16_27_37.jpg', 'Sara Gayle Carter', '<p>\r\n	Sarah Gayle Carter has been a spirited innovator in America&rsquo;s fast changing culture of design. Sarah Gayle Carter&rsquo;s range is broad, her vision clear, home furnishings her arena.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	Carter&rsquo;s aesthetic is grounded in well-mannered, neoclassical form and line. From there she lifts off into the atmosphere of things imagined and sophisticated color play.</p>\r\n', 8, 'yes', '', '', '<p>\r\n	1: Register for an account on this Website.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	2: Select All Options for this Design.<br />\r\n	Size, Finish, Mirror Plate and Qty.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	3: Request a Quote (A Formal Quote protects against Price Increases and may provide Promotional Pricing )<br />\r\n	After Requesting a quote you will have the opportunity to tell us about any special requests or modifications you wish to make to your design.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	Notes:- Finishes<br />\r\n	Actual Finish Samples Displayed on this website may be requested FREE once your order has been accepted. Max 3 Samples<br />\r\n	Matching Wood Finishes Requires that you send us a sample to match. Paint Finishes may be specified (Benjamin Moore or Sherwin Williams)<br />\r\n	Custom Finishes are available and subject to Quotation. If possible please send us a sample of your required finish.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	Finish Samples and our Finish Board are available to purchase prior to placing your order. (See Finishes Department at top of page)</p>\r\n', '', 'x', '', '', 'yes'),
(1189, 2, 'Federal Gallery', '', '', 'Federal mirrors and furniture date back to the Federal Period - the\r\nearly years of the United States government following its\r\nindependence from Britain in the late 18th and early 19th Centuries.<br>\r\nFederal style was the first truly American style but shares features\r\nwith European neoclassical styles. Both were inspired by classic\r\nGreek and Roman designs. <br>Federal furniture is made of wood and can\r\nbe characterized by its geometric designs, straight lines,\r\ncontrasting veneers, and colored inlays. The style often features\r\npictorial motifs of the early government such as an eagle, leaves,\r\nor lyres.<br> During this period, Federal style spread along the\r\nEastern coast of America with concentrations in New York,\r\nPhiladelphia, Boston, Baltimore, and Charleston. With our Federal\r\nmirrors, Friedman Brothers has striven to accurately preserve this\r\nhistorical design.<br> While many original pieces of Federal furniture\r\nare now being preserved in museums, a Federal mirror from Friedman\r\nBrothers allows you to own a piece of this history and display this\r\nbeautiful style. \r\n', 4, 'yes', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
