(592, 2, ' WILLIAMSBURG', '/images/temp_storage/2011_07_18_16_24_57.jpg', ' Williamsburg', '<p>\r\n	In the American colonies during the early 18th century, those who wanted to buy looking glasses usually had to buy English imports, whose already high prices were increased substantially with the cost of shipping.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	The craftsmanship to make a mirror&#39;s frame required great skill and expertise. For these reasons, mirrors were highly treasured, expensive possessions.</p>\r\n\"Friedman Brothers mastery of historical design has been the foundation of our licensing relationship since 1938, when the company first began creating reproductions of antique mirrors and sconces in the Colonial Williamsburg museums.  We value their understanding of the craft of mirror making, a trade that is quickly becoming a lost art.  Friedman Brothers offers discerning designers an outstanding array of mirrors with great beauty and integrity.\"<br>\r\nKris Fischer<BR>\r\nDirector of Licensing<br>\r\nThe Colonial Williamsburg Foundation\r\n', 10, 'yes', '', '', '<p>\r\n	1: Register for an account on this Website.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	2: Select All Options for this Design.<br />\r\n	Size, Finish, Mirror Plate and Qty.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	3: Request a Quote (A Formal Quote protects against Price Increases and may provide Promotional Pricing )<br />\r\n	After Requesting a quote you will have the opportunity to tell us about any special requests or modifications you wish to make to your design.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	Notes:- Finishes<br />\r\n	Actual Finish Samples Displayed on this website may be requested FREE once your order has been accepted. Max 3 Samples<br />\r\n	Matching Wood Finishes Requires that you send us a sample to match. Paint Finishes may be specified (Benjamin Moore or Sherwin Williams)<br />\r\n	Custom Finishes are available and subject to Quotation. If possible please send us a sample of your required finish.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	Finish Samples and our Fini