(277, 106, 'Antique Mirror', '', '', '<p>\r\n	Our antique mirror plate is hand created using chemical reactions over the silvering of the mirror. This process has many variables, including but not limited to, i) the manufacturer of the original mirror plate ii) ambient temperature and humidity during the process iii) time - the majority of the aging will occur during production but may continue to develop further in the coming months and years. iV) In addition the room lighting and angles viewed will change the appearance of the level of antiquing. Therefore it should be understood that variations will occur and no two samples will be alike. Antique mirrors made on the same day will be different. Samples shown on our website and provided for approval are to be taken as a rough guide to what can be expected.</p>\r\n', 10, 'yes', '', '', '', '', '', '/images/temp_storage/2011_08_05_13_29_58.jpg', 'DisplayOrder', ''),
