(1111, 53, 'Compos', '', '', '<p>\r\n	THE MAKING OF COMPO</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	STEP#1</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Weigh 25 lbs. Glue 1 1/4&quot; foamless</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Add 10 quartsx of hot water.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The glue and water go into a double boiler cooked at least 2 hours. Glue</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	has to be smooth liquid with no water or glue particles (like malasses).</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	In separate container, measure out 15 lbs. of pure gum dry rosin.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Add 10 lbs. boiled linseed.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Pour 2 ingredients in one 5 gallon pail.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Heat the above ingredient over gas heater in same can until melted and begining to boil, this takes at least 2 hours.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The rosin and linseed oil mixture is slowly poured into the cement mixer.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	(Pour before cement mixer is turned on).</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Then start the mixture, allowing to revolve until the linseed oil is cool enough. at that point, 21 ounces of liquid glycerine is added to the linseed and rosin mixture.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	This is allowed to turn several minutes until properly mixed.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Then mixture is shut off and the liquid glue is slowly poured into the mixture.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Mixture is started again and this is run until properly mixed and cooled.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	This takes about 10 minutes.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Mix is allowed to run and then slowly add 2-2 1/2 bags of whitting (100-125 lbs).</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	This makes a dough-like consistency.</p>\r\n', 1, 'yes', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
