(12, 'page', 'home', 'home', '<br />\r\n<a href=\"index.php?pid=13\" class=\"wikilink\">Home</a> <br />\r\n<a href=\"index.php?pid=14\" class=\"wikilink\">About Us</a> <br />\r\n<a href=\"index.php?pid=15\" class=\"wikilink\">Products</a> <br />\r\n<a href=\"index.php?pid=16\" class=\"wikilink\">Custom</a> <br />\r\n<a href=\"index.php?pid=17\" class=\"wikilink\">FAQ</a> <br />\r\n<a href=\"index.php?pid=18\" class=\"wikilink\">Contact US</a> <br />\r\n<a href=\"index.php?pid=19\" class=\"wikilink\">Handcrafting Process</a> <br />\r\n<br />\r\n<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"index.php?pid=20\">Test Area</a> <br />\r\n<br />\r\n <a href=\"index.php?pid=21\" class=\"wikilink\">CRM Glossary</a> \n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />', '2011-03-09 13:37:46'),
(13, 'page', 'Home', 'home/Home', '<br />\r\n<center>\r\n	<h3>\r\n		Welcome to Friedman Brothers Decorative Arts.</h3>\r\n</center>\r\n<p>\r\n	Since 1903, Friedman Brothers has been the World&#39;s premier creator of custom handcrafted decorative wall art for elegant interior design settings. Friedman Brothers products are found in some of the most prestigious locations around the World, including the halls of The Vatican and The White House. From private residences to World-class hotels, interior designers use Friedman products to enhance the prestige and elegance of their projects.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\n', '2012-05-03 15:04:50'),
(14, 'page', 'About Us', 'home/About Us', '<br />\r\n<center>\r\n	<u><font size=\"\\\"><strong>About Friedman Brothers</strong></font></u></center>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div align=\"\\\">\r\n	Friedman Brothers is the oldest and most prestigious manufacturer of handcrafted decorative wall art in the United States. The company has been family owned and operated for over 100 years, spending much of that history perfecting the art of Decorative Mirrors, Consoles, Sconces, Brackets, Cornices, Window Treatments and More.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	The company was founded by two brothers who emigrated from England in 1903. They brought with them an outstanding talent for old-world elegant design and the skilled crafts of wood carving and finishing, with special emphasis on Old World gold leafing. Through hard work and an unyielding commitment to design and quality, the Friedman brothers became the interior designer&#39;s supplier of choice for elegant and sophisticated decorative wall art.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	The brothers then passed down their craft through the generations where this same original commitment to design and quality can be found in the company&#39;s products today.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	Friedman Brothers decorative art is so high in quality that it can be found in the most prestigious places in the World, including Museums, The Vatican and The White House. From the best hotels to private residences, interior designers specify Friedman products to bring a touch of prestige and elegance to their designs.</div>\r\n<div align=\"\\\">\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li align=\"\\\">\r\n		<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"index.php?pid=14\">About Us</a></li>\r\n	<li align=\"\\\">\r\n		<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"index.php?pid=15\">Products</a></li>\r\n	<li align=\"\\\">\r\n		<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"index.php?pid=16\">Custom</a></li>\r\n	<li align=\"\\\">\r\n		<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"index.php?pid=17\">FAQ</a></li>\r\n	<li align=\"\\\">\r\n		<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"index.php?pid=18\">Contact US</a></li>\r\n	<li align=\"\\\">\r\n		<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"index.php?pid=19\">Handcrafting Process</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\n', '2012-01-10 04:49:02'),
(15, 'page', 'Products', 'home/Products', '<br />\r\n<center>\r\n	<u><font size=\"3\"><strong>Product Overview</strong></font></u></center>\r\n<br />\r\n<div align=\"justify\">\r\n	<br />\r\n	Friedman Brothers specializes in exquisite, high-end decorative wall art, which includes: Decorative Mirrors, Consoles, Sconces, Brackets, Cornices, Window Treatments, and more.&nbsp; All products are handcrafted the same way they were over 100 years ago, giving the finest attention to detail and quality not found in the mass-produced products of today. Each piece is truly an original work of art with unique character, detail, and an exquisite charm; which is why Friedman Brothers products are highly regarded as collectors items and appear in the most exclusive places in the World.</div>\r\n<br />\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"index.php?pid=14\">About Us</a></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"index.php?pid=15\">Products</a></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"index.php?pid=16\">Custom</a></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"index.php?pid=17\">FAQ</a></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"index.php?pid=18\">Contact US</a></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"index.php?pid=19\">Handcrafting Process</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\n', '2012-01-10 04:50:01'),
(16, 'page', 'Custom', 'home/Custom', '<br />\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n	<u><strong><font size=\"3\">Custom Options</font></strong></u></div>\r\n<br />\r\n<div align=\"justify\">\r\n	Can&rsquo;t find a product that precisely fits your design or do you need to match an antique? Friedman Brothers specializes in customizing products to a designer&rsquo;s exacting specifications.</div>\r\n<br />\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n	<strong>Custom Design</strong></div>\r\n<br />\r\n<div align=\"justify\">\r\n	Do you see a piece that you like but need it in a unique size? Would you like to subtly add or change elements on a particular piece to make it better suit your design? How about that one-of-a-kind, timeless antique you saw in a magazine, would you like a custom replica? Friedman Brothers can do all of these things and more! We personally handcraft each individual item so the sky is the limit for possibilities. What ever you can imagine, we can make it happen. For more information, contact us and we will be happy to make your custom design come true.</div>\r\n<br />\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n	<strong>Custom Finishes</strong></div>\r\n<br />\r\n<div align=\"justify\">\r\n	Whether you are matching existing antiques or furniture, or creating a truly original look, Friedman Brothers can match a finish to your precise specifications so it can be exactly what you desire for your design. Friedman Brothers products are also available in over 20 standard and premium finishes, including genuine gold, metal leaf, wood and paint finishes. The hand gilded finish is the most visible Friedman Brothers trademark. Gold, silver and metal leaf are masterfully applied in the traditional 18th century fashion, assuring heirloom quality for each mirror bearing the Friedman name. For more information, contact us and we will be happy to make your custom finish come true.</div>\r\n<br />\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n	<strong>Custom Sizes</strong></div>\r\n<br />\r\n<div align=\"justify\">\r\n	When browsing our huge selection of products, Friedman Brothers lists a wide range of sizes for each piece. If there isn&rsquo;t a size listed that meets your needs, we can customize any piece to meet the exact size you desire! We personally handcraft each individual item, which allows us the flexibility to make it exactly the way you want. For more information, contact us and we will be happy to make your selection in the size you need.</div>\r\n<br />\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n	<strong>Mirror Glass Options</strong></div>\r\n<br />\r\n<div align=\"justify\">\r\n	Mirror glass comes convex, plain, beveled, v-groove, engraved and colored. We also offer an option which simulates an antique presentation, which can come with a light antique, medium antique, or heavy antiqued appearance. The antiquing is done by hand and will always have subtle variations that can never be exactly replicated, offering a truly unique work of art.</div>\r\n<br />\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"index.php?pid=14\">About Us</a></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"index.php?pid=15\">Products</a></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"index.php?pid=16\">Custom</a></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"index.php?pid=17\">FAQ</a></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"index.php?pid=18\">Contact US</a></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"index.php?pid=19\">Handcrafting Process</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<br />\n', '2012-01-10 04:51:06'),
(17, 'page', 'FAQ', 'home/FAQ', '<br />\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n	Frequently Asked Questions</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n	<strong>About Catalogs and Brochures</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n	<strong>Q: <em>How do I order a Catalog?</em></strong><br />\r\n\r\n	A: Register for an account on our website and then contact us.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n	<strong>Q: <em>Why do you charge for your catalog?</em></strong><br />\r\n\r\n	A: Our catalog contains over 300 pages and costs over $50 to produce.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n	<strong>Q: <em>How do I update my catalog?</em></strong><br />\r\n\r\n	A: You can order missing pages. Contact us with a list of your missing pages. A small charge to cover our costs will apply.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n	<strong>Q: <em>I am a stocking dealer, do I still have to pay for my catalogs and updates?</em></strong><br />\r\n\r\n	A: No, active stocking dealers are provided catalogs and updates FREE.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n	<strong>Q: <em>Why can&#39;t I find designs on the website in your catalog?</em></strong><br />\r\n\r\n	A: It is not possible to catalog all of our designs, this website contains over 1,000 designs and we are constantly adding new designs, size options and finishes.&nbsp; Therefore the most up to date information can be found here.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n	<strong>About Price Lists</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n	<strong>Q: <em>How do I update Catalog Price Lists?</em></strong><br />\r\n\r\n	A: Register here for an online account and once approved you will be able to download current price lists.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n	<strong>Q: <em>What about online pricing, is that available?</em></strong><br />\r\n\r\n	A: Yes, and by invitation only to Trade Accounts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n	<strong>Q: <em>Do you give Trade Discounts?</em></strong><br />\r\n\r\n	A: Yes, Register Online and we will contact you.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n	<strong>About Finish Samples</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n	<strong>Q: <em>Can I order finish samples?</em></strong><br />\r\n\r\n	A: Finish samples are available FREE once an order is in place.&nbsp; You can view or purchase finish samples prior to making a purchase.&nbsp; Please contact us for further details.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n	<strong>Q: <em>Can you match a finish sample?</em></strong><br />\r\n\r\n	A: Yes, but in order to match to your requirements we request you send us a sample of the finish you require.&nbsp; We cannot blindly make finish samples based upon description only, their are too many variables to be successful.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n	<strong>About Products</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n	<strong>Q: <em>I am looking for a specific design but I cannot find it?</em></strong><br />\r\n\r\n	A: Call us on 800 327 1065, we have manufactured 1000&#39;s of designs and can probably help you further.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n	<strong>About Placing an Order</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n	<strong>Q: <em>How do I place an order?</em></strong><br />\r\n\r\n	A: Select your design and options,&nbsp; request a formal quote to fix the price based on your specifications.&nbsp; Further instructions will follow.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\r\n	<li>\r\n\r\n		<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"index.php?pid=14\">About Us</a></li>\r\n\r\n	<li>\r\n\r\n		<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"index.php?pid=15\">Products</a></li>\r\n\r\n	<li>\r\n\r\n		<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"index.php?pid=16\">Custom</a></li>\r\n\r\n	<li>\r\n\r\n		<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"index.php?pid=17\">FAQ</a></li>\r\n\r\n	<li>\r\n\r\n		<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"index.php?pid=18\">Contact US</a></li>\r\n\r\n	<li>\r\n\r\n		<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"index.php?pid=19\">Handcrafting Process</a></li>\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n	<br />\r\n\r\n	<br />\r\n\r\n	<br />\r\n\r\n	<br />\r\n\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n	<br />\r\n\r\n	<br />\r\n\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n', '2018-11-20 05:30:45'),
(18, 'page', 'Contact US', 'home/Contact US', '<br />\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" width=\"463\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td width=\"36\">\r\n				&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td valign=\"top\" width=\"410\">\r\n				<span class=\"Department_Title\">Contact Us</span><br />\r\n				<br />\r\n				<div class=\"pagetext\">\r\n					For more information, please contact us by clicking <a class=\"burgandyLink\" href=\"index.php?action=contact_form\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">here</font></a> or by phone using the numbers provided below:<br />\r\n					<br />\r\n					<br />\r\n					<span class=\"Department_Title\">Friedman Brothers Decorative Arts</span><br />\r\n					9015 N.W. 105th Way<br />\r\n					Medley, FL 33178<br />\r\n					Phone: (305) 887-3170<br />\r\n					Fax: (305) 885-5331<br />\r\n					Toll Free: (800) 327-1065<br />\r\n					Email: <a class=\"burgandyLink\" href=\"index.php?action=contact_form\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">click here</font></a><br />\r\n					Monday - Friday 8:00 - 6:00 Eastern Standard Time<br />\r\n					<br />\r\n					<br />\r\n					<span class=\"Department_Title\">High Point, North Carolina Showroom</span></div>\r\n				<p>\r\n					320 North Hamilton Street,<br />\r\n					High Point, NC 27260</p>\r\n				<p>\r\n					This location is the former TRS Showroom<br />\r\n					Directly across the street from Baker</p>\r\n				<div class=\"pagetext\">\r\n					<br />\r\n					Market Dates (Oct 12th - 17th)<br />\r\n					Contact: Clifford Poole</div>\r\n				<div class=\"pagetext\">\r\n					Cell Phone: 305 450 6679 &nbsp;</div>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\n', '2012-10-03 14:31:27'),
(20, 'page', 'Test Area', 'home/Test Area', '<br>\n&lt;br /&gt;<br />\r\n&lt;center&gt; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &lt;u&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to Friedman Brothers Decorative Arts.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/u&gt; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &lt;/center&gt; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;<br />\r\n&lt;div align=&quot;justify&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;<br />\r\nSince 1903, Friedman Brothers has been the World\'s &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; premier creator of custom handcrafted decorative wall art for elegant interior &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; design settings. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;<br />\r\n&lt;br /&gt;<br />\r\nFriedman Brothers products are found in some of the most &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; prestigious locations around the World, including the halls of The Vatican and &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The White House. From private residences to World-class hotels, interior &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; designers use Friedman products to enhance the prestige and elegance of their projects.&lt;br /&gt;<br />\r\n&lt;br /&gt;<br />\r\n&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;http://www.friedmanmirrors.com/images/marketing/CorniceSaleFeb2011.jpg&quot; /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />', '2011-02-01 18:54:46'),
(19, 'page', 'Handcrafting Process', 'home/Handcrafting Process', '<br />\r\n<center>\r\n	<font size=\"3\"><u><strong><span class=\"Department_Title\">Handcrafting Process</span></strong></u></font></center>\r\n<br />\r\n<p>\r\n	All Friedman Brothers products are constructed of the finest kiln dried woods. Artisans begin the first of the intricate and unique steps by precision cutting the pieces using carefully designed patterns. All wood joints are fitted carefully by hand to provide permanent bonded strength and to prevent warping. The product is then milled to its final shape.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	The next step is the application of the exquisite ornaments. The ornaments are handmade from a process dating back over 200 years and a very special gesso composition developed in the 18th century to achieve intricate ornamentation. Every ornament is bonded, tooled and handcrafted requiring the expertise of a skilled craftsman.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	Friedman Brothers is not only known for the quality of the ornamentation, but is considered a Master in the art of finishing. All our gilding is leafed by hand. Wood finishes are painstakingly stained and rubbed to give the precise color and patina required by our customers.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	We can also finish our products in the ornamental Chinoiserie style. We employ highly-skilled artists that are trained in the art of bas-relief hand-painted designs. All detailing, coloring and shading is done by hand to create a true one-of-a-kind piece of art.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	In summary, wood frames, gesso ornamentation, and water gilded hand burnished gold leaf are the signature of authentic museum quality reproductions crafted by Friedman Brothers.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"index.php?pid=14\">About Us</a></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"index.php?pid=15\">Products</a></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"index.php?pid=16\">Custom</a></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"index.php?pid=17\">FAQ</a></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"index.php?pid=18\">Contact US</a></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"index.php?pid=19\">Handcrafting Process</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<br />\r\n', '2018-11-20 05:31:40'),
